<HEADLINE> Swiss Police Seize Over 30 Kilograms of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Police in the Swiss city of
Zurich have seized 31.1 kilograms of heroin with a street value of
over 580,000 U.S. dollars and arrested three men, according to a
Swiss Radio International report Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Police took action Saturday after a search of two vehicles
yielded 32 packets of heroin, each weighing half a kilogram. Two
men were arrested, a police statement said.
</P>
<P>
Police then raided an apartment in Volketswil, belonging to the
parents of one of the men, and discovered a further 28 packets. A
third man was arrested at a separate location in Rumlang later
that day, and was found to be carrying 1,3 kilograms of the drug.
</P>
<P>
The three suspects, all in their early 20s, were not named, but
were said to be from former Yugoslavia. Two are residents in
Switzerland, and one lives in Germany.
</P>
<P>
Police said it was unclear whether the drugs were intended for
sale in Switzerland or were to be exported. They said the
investigation was continuing.
</P>
<P>
The seizure is a major victory for Zurich police, given that 51
kilograms of heroin were seized by Switzerland's border guards
over the whole of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
