<HEADLINE> Inflation In Britain Steadies In July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Inflation in Britain stayed
unchanged in July, easing fears that the Bank of England may move
to raise interest rates soon, according to official figures
released Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The key underlying inflation rate, used by the bank for setting
interest rates, was at 2.2 percent, comfortably below the
government's 2.5 percent target, the Office for National
Statistics said.
</P>
<P>
The headline rate of inflation, which includes mortgage rate
payments, also remained unchanged from June at 3.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
It is believed the rising cost of petrol had pushed the
headline inflation rate up to its highest level for nearly two
years in June.
</P>
<P>
In a report published last week, the Bank of England warned
that inflation would rise above the government's target over the
next two years. 
</P>
