<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Obtains 20-Billion-Yuan in Loan for Urban Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
will get a 20 billion-yuan loan over five years from the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China for its urban construction
projects.
</P>
<P>
Xu Qiyao, director of the provincial construction bureau, said
that the biggest bank loan contract ever in the province was inked
today between the provincial government and the Jiangsu branch of
the bank.
</P>
<P>
He said that Jiangsu plans to invest 175 billion yuan in
infrastructure projects over the next five years.
</P>
<P>
He said the province will seek more bank loans and foreign
investment for the province's urban construction.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu's urban construction will offer new opportunities for
foreign investors, he said. Meanwhile, the improvement of the
investment environment will also pave the way for attracting more
investors.
</P>
<P>
Over the next five years, Jiangsu Province will build an
additional 110 million square meters of highway, 10,000 kilometers
of water supply pipes and 65 million square meters of grassland,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The province will also build more sewage processing factories
and add 12,000 public buses in the next five years. 
