<HEADLINE> Sino-Vietnamese Border Highway Bridge Built up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A new border highway bridge
linking Hekou City in southwest China's Yunnan Province and Viet
Nam's Lao Cai Province was completed and open to traffic today.
</P>
<P>
The highway bridge, jointly built by the two sides, is l36.6
meters long and 15 meters wide and is the new border pass between
Hekou and Lao Cai.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side built 61 meters of the highway bridge with 8.44
million yuan of investment.
</P>
<P>
In the past, a railway bridge built in 1910 was the only
transportation link between Hekou and Lao Cai. The old bridge is
unable to keep up with the rapid growth of the bilateral trade.
</P>
