<HEADLINE> U.S. Envoy Plays Down Gap in Mideast Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, Aug 15 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Assistant Secretary of State
Responsible for the Middle East, Edward Walker, described here on
Tuesday the differences between the sides in the Middle East peace
process as "small."
</P>
<P>
The American envoy added in an upbeat tone that a compromise can
be reached between the Palestinians and Israel soon, reported the
Anatolia News Agency.
</P>
<P>
"Our optimism is that because the differences are somewhat
small, we will be able to reach an agreement in the not too distant
future," he said.
</P>
<P>
