These differences are critically important, foremost among them is
the question of Jerusalem."
</P>
<P>
Pointing out that important developments were recorded in the
summit between Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak and Palestinian
leader Yasser Arafat at Camp David last month, the senior U.S.
State Department official said, "our shared conviction is that this
is critically important for stability and the future of the
region."
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Walker held talks with Turkish Foreign
Minister Ismail Cem. But the two sides did not speak to reporters
after the talks.
</P>
<P>
Walker has already left Turkey for Morocco to continue his
diplomatic tour following the stalled Camp David summit.
</P>
<P>
Before him, Turkey received separately Palestinian leader Yasser
Arafat and Israeli Acting Foreign Minister Shlomo Ben-Ami, who came
in a row to brief Turkish leaders on the latest developments of the
peace process. 
