<HEADLINE> Singapore's Retail Sales Pick Up in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's overall retail
sales in June 2000 ran up to 2.72 billion Singapore dollars (about
1.60 billion U.S. dollars), rising significantly by 23.1 percent
year-on-year over a year ago and going up 10.2 percent compared
with the 2.47 billion Singapore dollars in the previous month,
according to data released by the Singapore Department of
Statistics Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The rise was mainly attributed to higher motor vehicle sales
which rose substantially by 23.3 percent over May 2000. Excluding
motor vehicles the index in June this year increased by 1.1
percent over the previous month and fell by 2.8 percent compared
to the same month of last year.
</P>
<P>
Sales of medical goods and toiletries surged up by 14.5 percent
month-on-month in June 2000 and dealers of recreational goods
reported a rise of 8.5 percent month-on-month in their turnover.
</P>
<P>
Retailers of wearing apparel and footwear registered a growth
of 7.4 percent month-on-month and business at food beverages and
furniture and household equipment retail outlets posted a 3.5
percent rise and 1.7 percent increase respectively in June this
year.
</P>
<P>
Sales of watches and jewelry sank by 12.1 percent in June over
May this year and supermarkets and retailers of optical goods and
books encountered respective falls of 5.6 percent and 1.8 percent
in revenue in the month.
</P>
<P>
Turnover of provision and sundry shops and telecommunications
and computers also declined by 1.4 percent and 1.0 percent
respectively in June.
</P>
<P>
The overall catering trade in June 2000 sank by 2.3 percent to
284 million Singapore dollars (about 167 million U.S. dollars)
compared with the 291 million Singapore dollars (about 171 million
U.S. dollars) in the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Compared to June 1999, the overall catering trade grew by 1.3
percent in June this year.
</P>
<P>
In June 2000, fast food outlets and restaurants recorded lower
sales of 7.9 percent and 2.6 percent respectively while sales at
other catering trade establishments remained unchanged over the
previous month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
