<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Glasses Have Hidden Trouble: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Results from the second quarter'
s selective examination of glasses shops show that only 65.7
percent examined shops are up to grade.
</P>
<P>
The State Bureau of Quality and Technical Supervision surveyed
143 groups of glasses from 143 eyeglass shops, and only 94 of them
qualified.
</P>
<P>
The survey also found out that about 94 percent of large
professional (chain) eyeglass shops, each with more than five
million yuan of annual sales, reached the qualification standards,
while only 31.8 percent small shops each with less than 500,000
yuan sales annually met the standards.
</P>
<P>
All the large professional shops are equipped with advanced
machines, high-precision detective facilities and self-contained
lens storage, all of which guarantees the quality of their glasses,
said the survey.
</P>
<P>
A major problem found out by the survey is that many small
shops sell substandard lens.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has urged departments concerned to increase efforts
to improve the quality of glasses.  
</P>
</TEXT>
