<HEADLINE> Romanian Capital Market Prepares for Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Romania's capital market
surveillance bodies are preparing more stimulating regulations for
investors this fall, which is a season when portfolio investments
traditionally increase, reported the local daily Curentul on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At present, the National Equities Commission and the National
Equities Association intend to create new regulations for the
operation of the Bucharest Stock Exchange and the RASDAQ over-the-
counter market.
</P>
<P>
The new regulations refer to the transactions of the two
markets, the decentralization of decisions and increasing the
attractiveness of the Romanian capital market.
</P>
<P>
According to the daily quoting stock exchange agents, a
solution to increase the liquidity on the capital market is to
provide a larger range of offers by quoting fixed income
instruments - bonds, T-bonds and municipal bonds. Such offers and
certain companies such as sports clubs will become extremely
attractive, stock exchange agents said.
</P>
<P>
Over the next period, the RASDAQ market will have two levels,
following the American NASDAQ model. The first level will operate
according to stock exchange principles and the second function as
an over-the-counter market for companies that no longer meet the
listing conditions.
</P>
<P>
After a compulsory shutdown that lasted 50 years, the Romanian
capital market was restored in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
