<HEADLINE> Slovak President Returns Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Slovak President Rudolf Schuster
returned home Tuesday after 48 days of treatment in Austria, the
Czech News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
After his plane landed in Bratislava, Schuster said that he has
felt the strength of Slovak citizens over the past few days, as "
the whole of Slovakia was living through it with me."
</P>
<P>
The president was accorded a warm welcome by Slovak Prime
Minister Migulas Dzurinda, parliament chairman Jozef Migas and
many ordinary citizens.
</P>
<P>
After he set foot again on the Slovak land, Schuster
symbolically kissed the ground. He appeared in good condition.
</P>
<P>
Schuster will soon fly to his hometown of Kosice in eastern
Slovakia to continue his convalescence.
</P>
<P>
Schuster, 66, underwent two emergency operations to repair a
perforated colon after he was hospitalized on June 14. His
condition deteriorated following complications after surgery.
</P>
<P>
The president was eventually moved to an Austrian clinic to
receive an emergency operation on June 28. After 35 days of
treatment, he was transferred to a nearby sanitarium. 
</P>
