<HEADLINE> Chinese Police Seize Book on Erotic Websites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese police have for the
first time confiscated certain volumes of "Special Websites," a
book specializing in listing erotic websites, the Ministry of
Public Security disclosed today.
</P>
<P>
The 191-page book contains more than 400 erotic websites in 24
categories, with detailed captions and pornographic pictures
attached to each website.
</P>
<P>
The book was recently found on sale in some bookstores in
Kunming and Dali, two scenic cities in Yunnan Province, southwest
China, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that by the end of June, China had registered
16.9 million web users, nearly doubling the figure a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Cracking down on the publication and trading of pornographic
books is one of the targets of the ongoing nationwide campaign
against prostitution, gambling, and narcotics trade, which was
kicked off on July 1 of this year. 
</P>
