overnight which rose on back of optimism that the United States
will leave interest rates unchanged when the Federal Reserve next
meets on August 22.
</P>
<P>
Most telecom and technology stocks rose on a technical rebound,
helped by the market's generally positive sentiment. Shares of
China Mobile, the mainland's number one wireless telecom firm,
extended mid-day gains and was up 4.18 percent in afternoon trade.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover totaled 11.353 billion HK dollars (1.455
billion U.S. dollars), slightly up from Monday's 9.74 billion HK
dollars (1.248 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indexes, Finance, Property and Commerce &AMP;
Industry rose 2.20 percent, 3.85 percent and 2.99 percent while
Utilities dropped 0.27 percent.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended with the Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index down 2.36 percent and the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corp
Index up 1.05 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index and Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index
increased by 3.41 percent and 1.33 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index gained 262.53 points, or 1.54
percent, to finish Tuesday's morning session at 17,260.59. Hong
Kong stocks rose 31.66 points, or 0.19 percent, to open at 17,029.
72 Tuesday. 
</P>
