<HEADLINE> Yahoo Ranks First for Home Internet Users in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 15 (Xinhua) -- An Internet measurement
company announced on Tuesday Hong Kong's 20 top websites in July
for home Internet users, among which Yahoo ranked first with 884,
000 unique users.
</P>
<P>
The report, said to be the first-ever user-based Internet usage
report for Greater China, was made by Internet measurement company
Iamasia based on the total number of unique users during the month
of July 2000.
</P>
<P>
Following Yahoo, Netvigator.com and Hongkong.com won second and
third places among the top 20, with 672,000 and 627,000 unique
users.
</P>
<P>
Info.gov.hk also entered Iamasia's top 20 websites list, ranking
13th with 413,000 unique users. Sina.com.hk ranked 16th, with 314,
000 unique users in the single month of July.
</P>
<P>
Iamasia, founded in 1999, is a provider of intelligence on
Internet usage in the Asia Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The information used for Iamasia's Hong Kong top 20 list is
based on data collected from the company's representative panel of
home Internet users in Hong Kong. 
</P>
