<HEADLINE> Supreme Procuratorate Alarms Party Members Against Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Communist Party
of China in procurators' offices, especially leading cadres, will
be educated about the spirit, work style and discipline of the
Party.
</P>
<P>
According to a notice issued by China's Supreme Procuratorate,
the education should last a half month in the third quarter of
this year and major corruption cases involving senior officials
such as Hu Changqing or Cheng Kejie should be used as materials.
</P>
<P>
It urged all Party members in the procuratorial sector to learn
a lesson from Cheng and Hu's cases by analyzing under what
conditions and how they started to travel down the road of
illegality.
</P>
<P>
The education is required to be combined with violations of
laws and rules of official conducts committed by some procurators
in recent years, said the notice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
