<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Provision Issued for Lawyer Qualification Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- China has issued new provision
for Qualification Test of Lawyer (QTL) this year, said an official
from the Ministry of Justice today.
</P>
<P>
The revised provision amended measures about test application,
the assigning of test questions, test paper printing, test and
grading.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the new QTL provision stipulates 14 test subjects,
including constitution, nomology, system and practice of lawyer.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a committee to assign test questions will be set
up and enrollment will be limited within a certain quota.
</P>
<P>
It is also said that test on foreign languages will be canceled
this time.
</P>
<P>
Until now, China has more than 100,000 certified lawyers and
more than 8,000 law offices.  
</P>
</TEXT>
