<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Boosts Investment in Electronic Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's investment in
electronic products and electrical appliances reached 38.4 billion
baht(960 million U.S. dollars ) in the first half of this year,
tripling the figure of the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The Board of Investment (BOI) said in an official report here
Tuesday that the amount is "the actual investment that has been
put into the construction of facilities and production lines that
are now running."
</P>
<P>
For the second half of the year, the BOI expects that the
booming investments in electronics will draw new investors.
</P>
<P>
Exports of electronic goods have powered Thailand's return to
economic growth after the infamous baht devaluation in July 1997
plunged the country into the worst recession in several decades.
</P>
<P>
The recent slide in the baht, the Thai currency, which lost 3.5
percent of its value in the April-to-June period, has given
exports an extra boost by making Thai goods, including electronic
products, cheaper in dollar terms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
