<HEADLINE> Vietnam Supports Middle East Peace Process: Vietnamese Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam supports the Palestinian
people's just struggle under the leadership of the Palestine
Liberation Organization (PLO) and the Middle East peace process,
Vietnamese President Tran Duc Luong said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In talks with visiting Palestinian President Yasser Arafat, who
arrived here Tuesday morning for a working visit, Luong also
expressed the hope that the negotiations between Palestine and
Israel will be restored as early as possible.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed that the Vietnamese party, state and people
consistently support the just struggle of the Palestinian people
under the leadership of the PLO in order to gain their inviolable
rights including self-determination, return to their homeland and
an independent Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
Luong noted that Vietnam supports the Middle East peace process,
all efforts aimed at reaching an equal and stable resolution of
the conflicts on the basis of resolutions 242 and 338 of the U.N.
Security Council and the land-for-peace principle.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese president also expressed his hope that the
negotiations between Palestine and Israel will be restored as
early as possible, reaching a final resolution for the occupied
land and establishing an independent Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Arafat informed Luong of recent Palestinian-
Israeli Camp David talks and Palestine's position.
</P>
<P>
Arafat left Hanoi Tuesday afternoon, concluding his short
working visit to Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
