<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Share prices ended higher on
Singapore Stock Market Tuesday boosted by gains in technology
counters which had recently fallen to bargain levels.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) rose 26.3 points to end
at the 2,153.44 in moderate trading.
</P>
<P>
The market volume totaled 413.61 million units worth 666.66
million Singapore dollars (389.86 million U.S. dollars). Advancing
issues outnumbered decliners by 202 to 120 with 241 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was an 18.87 million parcel by Achieva which
was transacted at 0.34 Singapore dollars per share. It was
followed by EWSport which had a volume of 14.84 million units done.
ST Assemb was the next with 13.04 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
