<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market Down on Tuesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- China's securities investment
fund market continued to move within corrections on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the 22 discounted funds, no one advanced and 12 of them
remained unchanged, according to China's leading financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Since last Thursday, the discounted funds had reversed its
courses with a negative bias. Except Fund Anxin, which insisted on
a corrective mode so far, other performers in the sector went down
either on profit-taking or on lack of confidence as investors saw
funds' interim reports delayed.
</P>
<P>
The seven restructured funds, after recent corrective movement,
started to consolidate. Five of them rallied in lackluster trading
while the other two remained unchanged. 
</P>
