<HEADLINE> Chinese T-bond Market Tuesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- China's treasury bond market
slacked Tuesday. Losers outnumbered gainers by four to two and the
transaction value shrank by 1.14 billion yuan to 1.56 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009704 tumbled by 0.19 percent at 145.14 yuan. Its yield
came to 3.87 percent, up 0.04 percentage points from Monday,
according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009905 and 009908 remained stable with contracted trade
volumes.
</P>
<P>
The ten-year floating-rate Bond 010004 dipped by 0.10 percent
to 104.4 after having climbed for seven-straight trading days,
pushing the yield up to 2.40 percent.
</P>
<P>
Lack of impetus, the repo market slumped following Monday's big
boom. Trade volume of three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-day
repurchasing transactions plummeted from 17.64 billion yuan to 1.
48 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
