<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-Share Market Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market
index dipped 0.53 points, or 0.72 percent to close at 75.72
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover was 56.62 million U.S. dollars, an increase of
10.02 million U.S. dollars, or 21.5 percent more than Monday's
total, according to Homeway, China's leading online financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market was consolidating around its best level since
October of 1997 on profit-taking action. The recent advance was
not hurdled as no sell-off was triggered so far and some effort
was mounted in late afternoon to trim losses.
</P>
