<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao SAR to Set Up Committee for Organizing Customs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Members of the committee include representatives from six
departments of the Macao SAR government, namely the Marine Police,
Economic Services, Statistics and Census Services, Public Security
Police, Security Forces and Postal Services, according to the
decree published Monday.
</P>
<P>
The committee will be headed by Choi Lai Hang, who has been
appointed chief of the customs one month ago by the State Council
following nomination by the Macao SAR's Chief Executive Edmund Ho
Hau Wah.
</P>
<P>
Major tasks of the preparatory committee include working out
the organizational structure of the customs and drafting necessary
legal documents. A preparatory work report is required to be
submitted to the chief executive by the end of November this year.
</P>
<P>
At present, customs functions are scattered among separate
government departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
