<HEADLINE> Cambodian Prime Minister to Visit Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen
will arrive in the Philippines on Wednesday for a three-day state
visit aimed at strengthening bilateral relations between Manila
and Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Presidential Palace said Tuesday in a statement
that the Cambodian leader's visit from August 16 to 18 will cover
Manila,Laguna, Cavite and the Subic Freeport in Zambales.
</P>
<P>
Highlighting Hun Sen's visit is his meeting on Wednesday with
President Joseph Estrada in the Presidential Palace, where he and
his delegation are expected to sign at least five agreements with
the Philippines, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The accords will cover cooperation in human resources and
health and the waiving of visas for bearers of diplomatic and
official passports, among others.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen is also expected to meet Philippine Vice President
Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo, Senate President Franklin Drilon and
Speaker Manuel Villar during his visit.
</P>
<P>
The Cambodian leader is scheduled to leave for Brunei on
Saturday via the Subic International Airport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
