<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Hits New Zealand, No Damage Reported </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake rocked
New Zealand's North Island Tuesday afternoon, but no damage has
been reported at this stage.
</P>
<P>
The New Zealand Institute of Geological and Nuclear Sciences
said in a press release that the earthquake, measured 7.3 on the
Richter scale, was 750 kilometers northeast of White Island off
the southeastern coastline of the North Island.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake was felt widely in the North Island and caused
computer screens to sway from side to side in Wellington.
</P>
<P>
It occurred at 4:33 p.m. but was deep, at a focal depth of 445
kilometers.
</P>
