<HEADLINE> Four Kenyan Policemen Nabbed over Robbery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Four Kenyan policemen in the
capital Nairobi have been arrested on charges of robbery and
extortion, bringing the number of police officers apprehended in
the past week to 10, the major newspaper Daily Nation reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The latest batch of four constables arrested were from one
police station and were behind an extortion racket targeting
traders and suspected criminals, police disclosed.
</P>
<P>
They include a sergeant and a corporal who were involved in the
fatal shooting of a policeman and the robbery of 12 million
shillings (about 160,000 U.S. dollars) from Kenya Railways on July
31.
</P>
<P>
The racket was exposed last Saturday when they arrested the
owner of a garage and demanded 8,000 shillings from him.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Nairobi Provincial Police Officer Geoffrey Muathe
said on Tuesday that a total of 12 suspects were being held over
the daylight robbery at Kenya Railways, in which the gang armed
with AK-47 assault rifles and sub-machine guns, ambushed a van
carrying salaries guarded by three railway security personnel,
killing a policeman nearby.
</P>
<P>
Observers here say that the Kenyan government is making efforts
to crack down on flagrant crimes perpetrated by policemen in order
to restore confidence of its people on police and create a
conducive environment for foreign investors. 
</P>
