Istanbul after the devastating earthquake which hit Marmara region
on August 17 of last year.
</P>
<P>
"The government did nothing for the quake victims in Istanbul.
We had collected 1.5 trillion lira (3 million U.S. dollars) in
Istanbul for the victims, but the government demanded this money
from us insistently. At last we sent it to Ankara," he added.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Daily News:
</P>
<P>
-- As terrorist groups were launching violence across the
Central Asian countries of Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan, Tajikstan and
Kazakhstan, Turkey is ready to give more support to those countries
in order to overcome the extreme religious terrorist threats
stemming from Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Yenibinyil:
</P>
<P>
-- An delegation of International Monetary Fund (IMF) is going
to visit Turkey on August 30 for the third time to review the
implementation of the 4-billion-U.S. dollar Stand-by Agreement
signed last year between Turkey and the IMF to support Turkey's
economic reforms and reduce its chronic inflation. 
</P>
