<HEADLINE> Stars Shine at Du Maurier Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- As many as 18 top singles players
in the world have committed to playing in Montreal for the 1.08
million U.S. dollars du Maurier Open women's tennis tournament,
which began Monday till Sunday, according to Canadian media.
</P>
<P>
Among the super stars shining on the list are four players
whose names have been engraved on the du Maurier Open champion's
hardware, including four-time champion Monica Seles, two-time
champion Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario, 1991 winner Jennifer Capriati
and reigning champion Martina Hingis.
</P>
<P>
From a ranking point of view, the top rivalry is between No.1
Martina Hingis of Switzerland and No.2 Lindsay Davenport of the
United States. Hingis and Davenport gained their top positions on
the Sanex WTA Tour heading into the North American hardcourt
campaign.
</P>
<P>
Both, however, are likely to face a series of stiff challenges
in pursuit of the title.
</P>
<P>
Another player in the limelight is the 18-year-old American
rising star, Serena Williams.
</P>
<P>
Both Serena and her sister Venus, 20, reached the semi-finals
of the U.S. open and that marked the first time sisters had
advanced that far in a Grand Slam event.
</P>
<P>
The William sisters repeated that feat this year at Wimbledon.
Venus, who missed the Canadian Open, beat Serena in the semis and
then Lindsay Davenport in the final.
</P>
<P>
The Wimbledon champion is reported to be absent from this year'
s du Maurier Open because younger sister Serena is entered.
</P>
<P>
When Serena was asked what fans could expect from her when she
made her first appearance in the du Maurier Canadian Open, she
replied, "Expect for me to be holding the winner's trophy."
</P>
<P>
More than 110,000 tickets had already been purchased before the
player list was released in the spring of 2000. A new high is
expected after Canadian tennis fans established a world-record
attendance of over 151,000 two years ago in Montreal for a single-
week, women's-only tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
