<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Judgment on Anwar's Defamation Suit Against Mahathir Reserved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's Court of Appeal
Tuesday reserved judgment on former deputy prime minister Anwar
Ibrahim's appeal against a High Court decision striking out his
defamation suit against Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad.
</P>
<P>
A three-member panel led by Ahmad Fairuz Sheikh Abdul Halim
decided to reserve judgment after hearing submissions from Anwar's
lawyer Karpal Singh, and Mohamed Adnan Shuaib for Mahathir.
</P>
<P>
The court said it would inform the parties of the date for the
decision and that the court would give a written judgment.
</P>
<P>
Anwar's 100 million ringgit (26.31 million U.S. dollar)
defamation suit filed on January 25 last year was struck out on
August 30 last year by High Court Judge R.K. Nathan on grounds
that it was frivolous and vexatious and an abuse of the process of
the court.
</P>
<P>
Anwar claimed in the suit that Mahathir had falsely and
maliciously spoken to local and foreign reporters at a news
conference at the Prime Minister's Department accusing him of
committing immoral act.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir contended in his statement of defence filed on March
22 last year that he spoke the words as prime minister on an
occasion of qualified privilege.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir's application to strike the suit out was allowed by
the High Court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
