<HEADLINE> China, Finland Sign New Agreement on Scientific Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences (CASS) and the Finnish Academy of Sciences (FAS) signed a
new agreement on cooperation for the years beginning 2001 to 2003.
</P>
<P>
The accord was signed by Vice-President of FAS Heikki Kallio
and his Chinese counterpart Wang Renzhi, who arrived here on
Saturday for a 5-day visit.
</P>
<P>
according to the new agreement, the two institutes will further
enhance an exchange of scientists, researchers and information,
and encourage branch research institutes to establish direct
relations.
</P>
<P>
The pacts were signed after a meeting between Kallio and Wang
on Aug. 15. Both sides agreed they were satisfied with the results
of previous cooperation in the social sciences and humanities
since they signed the primary agreement in 1990. China's
ambassador to Finland Lu Xinhua also joined the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by Wang Renzhi, is planning to visit
universities, research institutes, and museums in the near future.
The visit is expected to end on August 18. 
