<HEADLINE> Moldova Roots out Immigrants Trafficking Gang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Moldovan Ministry of the
Interior said it has destroyed a gang trafficking in illegal
immigrants; the gang reportedly has connections with high-ranking
officials, according to press reports reaching here Monday from
Chisinau, the Moldovan capital.
</P>
<P>
The gang has trafficked in more than 100 Moldovan illegal
immigrants to western countries at the charge of 1,700 U.S.
dollars per head since last December, said the Moldova news agency.
</P>
<P>
The news agency said the gang bribed officials from information
and security branches of the government to obtain clearance for
their illegal activities.
</P>
<P>
Authorities have found proof, such as lists of names of
possible illegal immigrants as well as fake seals and documents,
which include fake passports, from the homes of gang members, said
the news agency.
</P>
<P>
The Moldova news agency quoted Vladimir Turcanu, the Moldovan
Minister of the Interior, as saying that gang members could be
sentenced to 1-5 years in jail under the charge of forging
official documents and seals if they are judged guilty.
</P>
<P>
Officials involved in the trafficking activities will also be
punished, the Minister added. 
</P>
