<HEADLINE> Ukraine's GDP Grows 5 Percent in January-July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The real gross domestic product (
GDP) of Ukraine grew 5 percent during the first seven months of
this year, compared with the same period of 1999, the State
Statistics Committee said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The nominal GDP for January-July hit 87.44 billion hryvina (
about 15.9 billion U.S. dollars), including 16.1 billion hryvina (
about 2.9 billion dollars) for July, according to preliminary
reports.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the government expects a 2 percent GDP
growth for 2000.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, the country's GDP fell 0.4 percent. 
