<HEADLINE> Uruguayan Navy Suits Cargo Ship Skyros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Uruguayan navy has
brought a 16 million dollars suit against the cargo ship Skyros,
which ramed into the naval mine-sweeper "Valiente," press reports
said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Skyros, a cargo ship under Panamanian flag, and the Valiente
collided on August 5 off the coasts of the Rocha state, killing 11
sailors.
</P>
<P>
Rocha's justice court put into jail the captain of Skyros for
his absence in last week's trial, although he participated in
rescuing the victims.
</P>
<P>
Niver Lines, the company that built Skyros in 1977, termed as "
crazy" the 16 million dollars suit filed by the Uruguayan navy.
</P>
<P>
It was evaluating the possibility to leave the cargo ship at
the port of Montevideo, for Skyros has a value of 1.5 million
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
