<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thompson, Torres Repeat 1-2 Finish in 100m Freestyle Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Veteran Jenny Thompson and
Dara Torres repeated their dominance in the women's 100m butterfly
by finishing one-two anew in the finals of the 100m freestyle in
the U.S. Olympic swimming trials in Indianapolis Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
Thompson, 27, who was still seeking her first Olympic gold
medal away from the team events, again touched home first by
setting a new American record of 54.07 seconds in the 100m
freestyle finals.
</P>
<P>
Closely chasing behind was again the 33-year-old Torres, who
ended her seven-year retirement last year, in 54.62 seconds,
beating Ashley Tappin and Amy Van Dyken to third and fourth
respectively in 55.28 and 55.30.
</P>
<P>
Being the first American swimmer for four Olympic Games, Torres
was also hoping to reap her first Olympic gold medal from the
individual events after her appearences in the 1984, 1988 and 1992
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 200m individual medley, Tom Dolan also redeemed
his reputation by claiming the second straight title in 2:00.81,
after his victory from the 400m medley last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dolan, 24, a world record-holder in the 400m, failed to better
the American record of 2:00.11 in the 200m medley by a slim margin
of 0.27 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Tom Wilkens secured his second Olympic ticket by finishing
again in second place with a time of 2:01.38, after his silver-
medal finish in the 200m breaststroke on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
