<HEADLINE> DPRK Family Reunion Delegation Leaves for Seoul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of persons from
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), separated from
their families during the Korean War, left here on Tuesday morning
for Seoul.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by Chairman of the Central Guidance
Committee Ryu Mi-yong, consists of 100 separated-family members,
51 administrative, medical and security personnel, as well as
reporters.
</P>
<P>
During their three-day stay in Seoul, members of the delegation
will reunite with family members or relatives with whom they were
separated before or during the Korean War (1950-1953).
</P>
<P>
At the historic inter-Korean summit in Pyongyang on June 13-15,
DPRK leader Kim Jong Il and South Korean President Kim Dae-jung
agreed on a reunion of separated families on August 15, a date
selected to coincide with the 55th anniversary of Liberation Day
from Japanese colonial rule. 
