<HEADLINE> Chinese High-Tech Start-up Eyes SESDAQ Listing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai-based Bitsoft Co., Ltd.
is aiming to become the first Chinese high-tech start-up to be
listed on SESDAQ, the second board market of Singapore, China
Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
"Currently, we have already shown strong interest and made
informal applications to the China Securities Regulatory
Commission, the regulatory authority of China's stock market,"
company general manager Fu Zhangqiang was quoted as saying Monday.
</P>
<P>
The company has formed a group responsible for bringing the
business in line with market requirement, Fu said, adding that he
hopes Bitsoft would be listed within a year.
</P>
<P>
Established in December 1998, the company has been growing fast,
with turnover exceeding seven million yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Its flagship product is a series of software products for law
firms. Bitsoft wants to sell overseas later.
</P>
<P>
"Our goal is to take at least 50 percent of the legal software
market share within two to three years," Fu said.
</P>
<P>
To prepare for SESDAQ listing, the company is negotiating with
a number of venture investors, Chinese government-funded firms and
private companies.
</P>
<P>
Fu said the company plans to raise 20 to 30 million yuan to
swap no less than 30 percent of its total shares through venture
capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
