<HEADLINE> Meningitis Hits Central Rwanda, Killing 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 16 (Xinhua) -- A meningitis epidemic is hitting
the central Gitarama Prefecture of Rwanda and 20 people have
reportedly died, Rwanda News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Health has started a four-day immunization
program in the most hit Commune of Tambwe. Bernard Nzigiye, the
medical officer in the area, was quoted as saying that the program
is intended to cover those without meningitis symptoms and about
16,400 people will be immunized.
</P>
<P>
The immunization against meningitis follows another recent
campaign through which 800,000 Rwandan young children were
immunized against polio and measles. 
</P>
