<HEADLINE> Nigerian Foreign Exchange Reserves Rise to 7 Billion U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's foreign exchange
reserves reached 7.136 billion U. S. dollars at the end of June
this year, the Central Bank of Nigeria said in a report.
</P>
<P>
The report, which was available here on Wednesday, said the
foreign exchange reserves increased by 900 million dollars in June.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the main inflow of the country's
foreign exchange was from oil exports, while the main outflow was
for external debt service, national priority projects and cash
calls from commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
When President Olusegun Obasanjo took over power last May,
Nigeria's foreign reserves were almost in red, due to the spending
spree of the former military government. 
</P>
