<HEADLINE> Ugandan Rebels Behead 10 Civilians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The Allied Democratic Forces (
ADF) rebels, who attacked a trading center and a health center in
Hoima district in western Uganda Friday night and abducted 25
civilians, have so far killed 10 of them.
</P>
<P>
The Monitor daily reported Wednesday that the rebels killed
their captives by beheading.
</P>
<P>
According to a survivor, Adebo Clement, a teacher of Nyakaseke
primary school and now admitted in Hoima hospital with multiple
wounds, the rebels first killed Tindyebwa Christopher, chairman of
the Local Council of Nyakaseke on the night they were captured.
</P>
<P>
"The ten were slaughtered like goats," said Adebo, adding that
other captives were still in rebel captivity being used to carry
the loot.
</P>
<P>
The rebels, about 40 of them, shot dead a nurse and a Ugandan
army veteran after they forcefully broke into a health center in
Kabwoya sub-county Friday night.
</P>
<P>
They abducted 25 civilians, among Local Council officials and
school teachers, who were forced to head for the Bitagata forest
in the area.
</P>
<P>
The ADF rebels stole all the drugs stored in the health center
and looted people of much money and shop items, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The rebels, who are based in the eastern Democratic Republic of
the Congo, have been fighting against the Ugandan government and
conducting anti-government activities in western Uganda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
