<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Fall Mostly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mostly
lower Tuesday with the Dow Jones industrial average falling on
profit-taking. The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose a
bit.
</P>
<P>
At the close of session, the Dow index fell 109.14 at 11,067.00,
eliminating much of the 148.34-point surge Monday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly lower. The Standard &AMP; Poor
's 500 index fell 7.13 at 1,484.43 but the Nasdaq composite rose 1.
97 at 3,851.66.
</P>
<P>
The Dow index fell as investors pulled some money out of the
market to lock in profits from recent rallies. The blue chip index
rose 270.31 points in the previous three sessions in a raw,
crossing the threshold of 11,000 last Friday for the first time
since April 25.
</P>
<P>
Investors took profits as they await a meeting of the Federal
Reserve on the monetary policy. Analysts have widely expected the
central bankers to leave interest rates unchanged at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
A new report gave investors more confidence in steady rates.
The Federal Reserve reported today that the U.S. industrial
production rose 0.4 percent in July, in line with analysts'
expectations, showing little sign of inflation.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Reserve has raised rates six times since last
summer in an effort to cool off the economy and keep inflation
under control.
</P>
<P>
Among retailers, Home Depot and J.C. Penney fell today,
dragging the Dow lower. But Applied Material and Texas Instruments
in the tech section led the Nasdaq's advance.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE fell 4.04 at 668.01 and the American Stock Exchange
index fell 16.09 at 912.78. The Russell 2000 index of smaller
companies fell 4.55 at 509.93.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 7-to-5 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,697 down, 1,167 up and 492
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 891.88 million shares from 781.64
million in the previous session.  
</P>
</TEXT>
