<HEADLINE> Argentine Stocks Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index on
the Buenos Aires Exchange Tuesday closed down 1.97 percent at 478.
94 points compared with last Friday's 488.57 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 79.074 million U.S. dollars against 38.078
million dollars in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The annual inter-bank interest rate increased to 7.25 percent
from Monday's 7.15 percent in the 24-hour term. The exchange rate
of the Argentine peso against the U.S. dollar stood at 0.996 for
purchase and 1.001 for sale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
