<HEADLINE> Sao Paulo Stocks Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on the Sao Paulo
Securities Exchange, the largest in Latin America, closed down
Tuesday with the key Bovespa Index falling 0.37 percent to 17,744
points from Monday's 17,810.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged shares worth 502 million U.S. dollars against
506 million dollars in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of the local currency, the real, stood at 1.
802 for one U.S. dollar for purchase and 1.805 for sale.  
</P>
</TEXT>
