<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Regional Integration Helpful to Bring Lasting Peace to Africa: EU Diplomat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- European Union Ambassador to
Zambia Jorgen Krebs said on Wednesday that regional integration
through regional groups such as Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA) would bring lasting peace to the African
continent riddled with armed conflicts.
</P>
<P>
He said political will and commitment to regional integration
as a basis of enhancing economic growth and welfare would help
overcome conflicts afflicting the continent.
</P>
<P>
Krebs made the remarks at a news briefing in Lusaka on the
forthcoming COMESA-EU Trade and Investment Exhibition scheduled
for October 26-31 this year.
</P>
<P>
Krebs also said trade and regional integration had been an
essential element for European/African dialog, which began in
Cairo in April this year.
</P>
<P>
He noted that there was need to foster inter-regional
relationships to boost inter-regional trade in line with
globalization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
